#summary Information about the Keyboard component.

= Introduction =

The Keyboard component gives the entity access to the key states. With its condition, the user can trigger a script when a key is pressed.

= Parameters =
This component has no parameters.

= Condition =

Pressed keys are what make Keyboard conditions positive. A single key can be specified, or either all keys through the "all" parameter.

|| *Parameter* || *Type* || *Description* ||
|| key         || int    || The key that will make the condition positive ||
|| all         || bool   || If true, any key will make the condition positive ||

Note that with the omega parameter you can set key repetition.